tasks.description:
Add Results input types and extend RefVerifyDriver in the cli_driver layer. Depends on: T003. (1) Add RefVerifyChainSelect enum in apps/cli-driver/src/ref_verify.rs with variants: Chain1, Chain2, All. Derives: Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq. Module path: cli_driver::ref_verify. (2) Add RefVerifyVerdictSelect enum with variants: FailPending, Pass, Fail, Pending, All. FailPending is used when the CLI omits --filter. Derives: Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq. (3) Add RefVerifyResultsInput struct with fields: track_id: String, items_dir: std::path::PathBuf, chain: RefVerifyChainSelect, layer: String (plain String, 'all' or a layer name), verdict: RefVerifyVerdictSelect. Derives: Debug, Clone. (4) Add Results(RefVerifyResultsInput) variant to RefVerifyInput enum. (5) Extend RefVerifyDriver::handle() match to dispatch RefVerifyInput::Results(input) -> self.ref_verify_results(input). (6) Add ref_verify_results private method that: converts RefVerifyChainSelect to usecase::ref_verify::RefVerifyChainFilter, converts RefVerifyVerdictSelect to usecase::ref_verify::RefVerifyVerdictFilter, converts the layer argument after chain selection so Chain1 always uses RefVerifyLayerFilter::All without validating the raw layer string (AC-08 no-op), while Chain2/All convert layer String 'all' to RefVerifyLayerFilter::All and any other string to RefVerifyLayerFilter::Specific(LayerId::try_new(...)?) propagating validation errors as CommandOutcome::failure; calls self.service.results(track_id, items_dir, chain_filter, layer_filter, verdict_filter); on Ok, renders the RefVerifyResultsOutput as a text string: first block (one line per lane in lane_summaries: '  {label}: pass={pass_count} fail={fail_count} pending={pending_count}'), blank line, record block (one entry per pair_record, each as 'claim: {claim_hash_hex}
evidence: {evidence_hash_hex}
verdict: {verdict_label}
reason: {reason}
chain+layer: {chain_layer}
claim_origin: {origin_display}
evidence_origin: {origin_display}
'), final Summary line: 'Summary: {total_pass} pass, {total_fail} fail, {total_pending} pending, {total} total'; returns CommandOutcome::success with exit_code 0 (always, per CN-02); on Err(RefVerifyDriverError::Wiring), returns CommandOutcome::failure; on other Err, returns CommandOutcome::failure. (7) Add a format_origin_display private free function that formats VerifyOriginRef as a human-readable string: SpecElement -> 'spec:{section_kind}:{element_id}:{text_label_truncated}', AdrDecision -> 'adr:{file_path}#{decision_id}', CatalogueEntry -> 'catalogue:{file_path}:{section_key}:{entry_key}'. (8) Add unit tests for: format_origin_display for each variant, chain/verdict/layer conversion including FailPending and Chain1 with a non-layer raw string being ignored as RefVerifyLayerFilter::All, rendering of empty lane_summaries and empty pair_records, summary line format. Catalogue refs: cli_driver-types.json RefVerifyChainSelect, RefVerifyVerdictSelect, RefVerifyResultsInput, RefVerifyInput, RefVerifyDriver. Spec refs: IN-01, IN-02, IN-03, IN-06, AC-01, AC-05, AC-07, AC-08, AC-09, AC-10, CN-01, CN-02, CN-04.
